    "description": "A few tips: We find the salt a little too much and usually adjust it down to 1.5 tsp or less per pound of pork. This dish has a little heat from the red peppers, but if you like spicy add a dash or two of cayenne pepper! And as always, be sure to use the flour to thicken the broth AFTER pressure cooking. Hope y'all enjoy!",
